OL,6,FMs Black said: "While it has not been
OL,7,Fpossible to avoid an increase in rates
OL,8,Fagain this year, all parties have
OL,9,Fworked hard to keep this year's rise
OL,10,Fas low as possible.J"Like everyone,
OL,11,Four council is impacted by the cost-of-
OL,12,Fliving crisis and continued high
OL,13,Fprices for energy, insurance and other
OL,14,Fservices, but we have delivered
OL,15,Fsignificant savings in order to absorb
OL,16,Fsome of those external pressures,
OL,17,Fwhile also supporting our own staff
OL,18,Fwho deliver so many key services for
OL,19,Four city.J"This increase will allow us
OL,20,Fto support our council workers with
OL,21,Ffair pay and also invest in
OL,22,Fimprovements which will make a real
OL,23,Fdifference to citizens. These include
OL,24,Fthe expansion of glass recycling
OL,25,Fprovision, funding towards new and
OL,26,Fimproved pitches for sports clubs,
